President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump have announced the reopening of public tours at the White House. These tours can be requested through Members of Congress, with requests accepted up to three months in advance. The tours are self-guided and last approximately 45 minutes. They are available on a first-come-first-served basis. The tour hours are from Tuesday to Thursday, 7:30 AM to 11:30 AM, and Friday to Saturday, 7:30 AM to 1:30 PM. More information can be found at https://trumpwhitehouse.archives.gov/participate/tours-and-events. The Visitors Office information line is also available at 202-456-7041.